AKURE – The immediate past Chairman of Social Democratic Party (SDP) in Ondo State, Prince Dele Ogunbameru, has denied the allegation that he was once suspended from the party. This was contained in a statement he signed on Friday and made available to newsmen in Akure, the Ondo State capital. Ogunbameru made the denial while reacting to a statement credited to Dr. Olu Agunloye, the party’s National secretary. -Advertisement- Agunloye had in his reaction to Chief Olu Falae’s comment on the party in which he(Falae) said anyone who claimed to be the national chairman of the party was floating on water. Ogunbameru said: “The statement credited to Chief Olu Falae is nothing but the truth and a rebuttal can only come from a man like Agunloye who I brought into the party to contest the 2016 election. “On the allegation that I was suspended from the party, I was never suspended from the SDP. I left the party at a time taking half of the structure with me because I was not comfortable with people like Agunloye and the way he was dividing the party.” The SDP chieftain claimed that Dr. Agunloye escaped suspension by swapping position with the party’s nation’s secretary. He said: “Dr. Agunloye has been suspended as a member of the SDP but to stay on, he had pledged 100% loyalty and swapped position with the former National Secretary, Alhaji Shehu Gabam.”